title: For Sale:  Browning A-Bolt 338 Win Mag w/BOSS
location: Grand Island, NE, Grand Island, Nebraska
postcontent: Browning A-Bolt 338 Win Mag w/BOSSThe classic browning A-Bolt delivers dependable pinpoint accuracy that esceeds the stringent standards of the modern rifleman. The renowned A-bolt has a short 60 degree lift that incoporates a non-rotating bolt sleeve that runs the entire length of the bolt. When unlocked three guide ribs on the bolt sleeve align with the three lugs to allow the bolt to slide smoothly. When locked these lugs provide massive bolt strength. The bolt feeds smoothly because of the unique patented cartridge depresor that stays in positoin independent of th ebolt rotation as the bolt slides gently over the cartridges in the magazine. The bolt face is recessed completely surrounding the cartridge base. A cocking indicator locatd at the rear of the bolt offers visual firing pin status. The barrel is free floated and glass bedded at the recoil lug and front of the receiver to maintain the proper spacing around the barrel for consistent accuracy. Barrels are triple checked for interior finish, straightness and air-gauged for uniformity. The Boss SystemBallistic Optimizing Shooting System is a tunable option on this model. Rest assured once the concept is understood you will be using you BOSS equipped rifle and making adjustments on the fly like a pro and achieving top accuracy with all the loads you like. When you find a new load that you like it will only take a few groups and you will have your BOSS - and your rifles accuracy- tuned in to perfection. No other accuracy enhancement puts the power in the hands of the shooter like the BOSS does. BOSS theory indicates that moving the BOSS device along the barrel changes the vibration frequency or "Sweet Spot". The "Sweet Spot" is when the bullets exits the barrel at the top or bottom, as opposed to the middle of the wave, which are the times the barrel experiences the least amount of motion. Precision accuracy from the BOSS system is acheived by calibrating your rifle and ammo to your "Sweet Spot" setting. Video available online.

For quick, close-range shooting the 1895SBL comes with an excellent XS ghost ring, rear aperture sight mounted to the rail, and a front post with white line up the center. These sights are extremely rugged and do not get knocked out of alignment easily. A Pachmayr® Decelerator® recoil pad helps absorbs recoil from heavy .47-70 rounds, allowing shooter to stay on target for fast follow up shots. A receiver-mounted crossbolt safety effectively blocks the hammer from hitting the firing pin. Sling swivel studs allow for the attachment of a rifle sling for convenient carry in the field with the hands free. Marlin 1895SBL is a very quick-handling Lever-Action Rifle that shoots a cartridge powerful enough to knock down any species of game in North America. The 1895SBL is built to hold up to rugged use in harsh environments. Made in USA. Manufacturer model #: 70478. title: For Sale:  Gen 3 CAA Micro Roni Stab for Glock 19
postcontent: Very lightly used CAA Micro Roni Stab for a Glock 19.  I used my Gen 4 in it, and it worked like a champ.  Comes with the box.  No sites on it - you'll need to get some irons, or a red dot (I ran a Primary Arms advanced micro dot on mine - but am keeping it).  This thing rode around in my truck, along with a couple of fun sticks as my "get home gun" if I needed it.  It is a blast to shoot, and greatly extends the accurate range of your Glock.Price is $230, firm.  I won't respond to any questions like "what's your best price?  will you take (insert any number less than $230 here)?"Can meet in Franklin over the next week or so, and then Smryna during the day.If you have questions about what this is, I suggest you Google "CAA Micro Roni Stab," and there will be a bunch of info.  This is the model that includes the stabilizer brace, so no SBR tax stamp is required.
